Portion-Shadowblade extrodinare. Come PL me u sucker's</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubraincandy999.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Braincandy999</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.austin.rr.com/pagedir/tinyeye.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 12:05:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2023.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions about Armor Crafting *midgard*</span><hr size=1> Tailors are needed for the chain armor.  If he plans on just doing consignment(tasks) then he will get chain armor requests and will need to have leather components made.  If he plans to Plevel, he can do only studded items which don't require leather armor (just require leather squares)<br>
<br>
You can purchase the leather from vendors (up until the upper echelon of crafting) and still make a profit on the final chain piece.  You will make a bigger profit margin if you purchase the items from a reasonably priced player tailor.<br>
<br>
The biggest benefit to an armorer who also does his own tailoring, IMHO is that once they get to 500+ this one person can make 2/3 of the siege equipment needed to make a siege engine.<br>
